1. Definitions

  1.1 "You" (or "Your") means an individual or legal entity exercising
      permissions granted by this License.

  1.2 "Organization" means the legal entity on whose behalf You use the
      Software, and all entities that control, are controlled by, or are
      under common control with that entity. For purposes of this
      definition, "control" means (i) ownership of fifty percent (50%) or
      more of outstanding shares or beneficial ownership, or (ii) the
      power to direct management of the entity.

  1.3 "Annual Recurring Revenue" or "ARR" means the Organization's
      gross revenue from all sources over the trailing twelve (12) months,
      as reasonably determined by the Organization.

  1.4 "Employees" means the Organization's full-time equivalent staff
      count, including employees, contractors working substantially
      full-time, and affiliates counted as a single Organization under
      Section 1.2.

  1.5 "Production Environment" means any deployment of the Software
      used to store, serve, or process data for operational purposes,
      excluding Development and Testing Environments.

  1.6 "Development and Testing Environment" means a deployment used
      solely for local development, automated testing, continuous
      integration, quality assurance, or staging that is not used to
      serve production workloads or external users.

  1.7 "Open-Source Project" means a software project whose source code
      is publicly distributed under a license approved by the Open Source
      Initiative (<https://opensource.org/licenses>), and where Your use
      of the Software is solely to develop, build, test, or distribute
      that Open-Source Project.

  1.8 "Third-Party Access" means providing access to the Software, or
      to repositories or services operated through the Software, to
      individuals or organizations outside Your Organization. Internal
      use by employees, contractors, and affiliates of Your Organization
      does not constitute Third-Party Access.

  1.9 "Commercial License" means a written agreement with the
      copyright holders granting production rights beyond this License.
      See COMMERCIAL-LICENSE.md.

1. Grants

  Subject to the terms of this License, the copyright holders grant You
  a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to:

  (a) use, copy, and modify the Software;

  (b) compile the Software into object form;

  (c) distribute unmodified or modified source code of the Software;

  (d) use the Software in Development and Testing Environments without
      restriction;

  (e) use the Software in a Production Environment when all of the
      following apply:
      (i)   the deployment is for internal use by Your Organization;
      (ii)  the deployment does not provide Third-Party Access;
      (iii) Your Organization has ARR below one million US dollars
            ($1,000,000); and
      (iv)  Your Organization has three hundred (300) or fewer
            Employees; or

  (f) use the Software in a Production Environment for an Open-Source
      Project, regardless of Your Organization's ARR or Employee count,
      provided the use is solely for that Open-Source Project as defined
      in Section 1.7.

  You may keep Your modifications private. You are not required to
  publish or share modifications, subject to Section 3.

1. Restrictions

  Without a valid Commercial License, You may not:

  (a) use the Software in a Production Environment if Your Organization
      has ARR of one million US dollars ($1,000,000) or more, or more
      than three hundred (300) Employees, except as permitted under
      Section 2(f) for Open-Source Projects;

  (b) use the Software in a Production Environment that provides
      Third-Party Access, including managed hosting, software-as-a-
      service, platform-as-a-service, resale, or any offering that
      makes the Software available to parties outside Your Organization,
      regardless of Your Organization's ARR or Employee count;

  (c) use the OpenGitBase name, logo, or other trademarks except as
      permitted in TRADEMARK.md;

  (d) remove or obscure copyright, license, or attribution notices in
      the Software.

  Modifications to the Software remain subject to this License. You may
  not sublicense the Software on terms that remove or conflict with
  this License.

